形为乐器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-human-body-morph-into-musical-instruments-from-around-the-world-at-a-new-exhibition-at-the-metropolitan-museum-of-art-180988931/</link><description>在这场解剖艺术史展览中，腹部变成了鼓，双手变成了打击工具，脸变成了铜钟</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 19:41:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-human-body-morph-into-musical-instruments-from-around-the-world-at-a-new-exhibition-at-the-metropolitan-museum-of-art-180988931/</guid></item><item><title>研究人员调查了永久冻土中冷冻的古松鼠粪便，发现了有关动物生态系统的启发性细节</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-investigated-ancient-squirrel-poop-frozen-in-permafrost-and-found-enlightening-details-about-the-animals-ecosystem-180988934/</link><description>早在 70 万年前，现代加拿大的地松鼠就通过饮食收集了大量有关其过去环境的有用遗传信息</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 18:47:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/researchers-investigated-ancient-squirrel-poop-frozen-in-permafrost-and-found-enlightening-details-about-the-animals-ecosystem-180988934/</guid></item><item><title>疏浚萨凡纳河的工人偶然发现了自独立战争以来一直在水下的 19 门大炮</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/workers-dredging-the-savannah-river-stumbled-upon-19-cannons-that-had-been-underwater-since-the-revolutionary-war-180988928/</link><description>这些具有数百年历史的文物于 2021 年至 2022 年间从河床中浮现出来。专家们花了数年时间精心修复了其中 17 件，这些文物将在新展览中首次公开亮相</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 18:13:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/workers-dredging-the-savannah-river-stumbled-upon-19-cannons-that-had-been-underwater-since-the-revolutionary-war-180988928/</guid></item><item><title>您很快就可以用 12,060 块乐高积木搭建圣家堂。这就是为什么著名的大教堂是一个建筑奇迹</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/you-can-soon-build-the-sagrada-familia-out-of-12060-legos-heres-why-the-famed-basilica-is-an-architectural-marvel-180988927/</link><description>先锋建筑师安东尼·高迪对大教堂的规划雄心勃勃且复杂，借鉴了创造性的几何形式和古老的灵感，这也是它在 144 年后仍未完工的原因之一</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 17:44:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/you-can-soon-build-the-sagrada-familia-out-of-12060-legos-heres-why-the-famed-basilica-is-an-architectural-marvel-180988927/</guid></item><item><title>大黄蜂可以即时解决问题，为昆虫的令人印象深刻的认知能力增添了色彩</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-can-solve-problems-on-the-fly-adding-to-the-insects-list-of-impressive-cognitive-abilities-180988925/</link><description>在一系列实验中，模糊传粉者弄清楚了如何使用球作为获取含糖食物的工具。这项研究进一步强调，尽管这些生物的大脑很小，但它们却相当聪明</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bumblebees-can-solve-problems-on-the-fly-adding-to-the-insects-list-of-impressive-cognitive-abilities-180988925/</guid></item><item><title>500 年前，列奥纳多·达·芬奇的笔记本被切碎并分离。现在，发明人的手稿和图纸在在线档案中被重建</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/500-years-ago-da-vincis-notebook-was-cut-up-and-separated-now-the-inventors-manuscripts-and-drawings-are-reconstructed-in-an-online-archive-180988922/</link><description>伽利略博物馆研究人员开发的一种新工具恢复了几个世纪前切除的碎片中的 50 页</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 02:35:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/500-years-ago-da-vincis-notebook-was-cut-up-and-separated-now-the-inventors-manuscripts-and-drawings-are-reconstructed-in-an-online-archive-180988922/</guid></item><item><title>NASA 宣布阿耳忒弥斯 3 号机组人员包括四名宇航员，他们将在近地轨道“承担经过计算的风险”，为未来登月铺平道路</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-announces-the-crew-of-artemis-3-four-astronauts-who-will-take-calculated-risks-in-low-earth-orbit-and-pave-the-way-for-a-future-moon-landing-180988920/</link><description>该任务预计将于明年发射，将练习与 SpaceX 和 Blue Origin 开发的月球着陆器会面和对接</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 20:53:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-announces-the-crew-of-artemis-3-four-astronauts-who-will-take-calculated-risks-in-low-earth-orbit-and-pave-the-way-for-a-future-moon-landing-180988920/</guid></item><item><title>这枚罕见而复杂的胸针代表了罗马帝国征服苏格兰的漫长而杂乱的尝试</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-intricate-brooch-represents-the-roman-empires-long-disjointed-attempt-to-conquer-scotland-180988923/</link><description>这件“微型杰作”将在即将举行的展览中展出，该展览的重点是罗马在被称为喀里多尼亚的高地留下的遗产</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 19:55:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-intricate-brooch-represents-the-roman-empires-long-disjointed-attempt-to-conquer-scotland-180988923/</guid></item><item><title>一项新的研究表明，不同文化背景的人们都认为女性的面孔比男性的面孔更具吸引力</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-across-cultures-find-womens-faces-to-be-more-attractive-than-mens-a-new-study-suggests-180988914/</link><description>在许多野生动物物种中，雄性比雌性具有更华丽的特征，以帮助它们吸引配偶。但科学家们很早就注意到，人类似乎是个例外，女性常常被认为是“更公平的性别”</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 19:14:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/people-across-cultures-find-womens-faces-to-be-more-attractive-than-mens-a-new-study-suggests-180988914/</guid></item><item><title>“可爱的小家伙”：科学家在加拉帕戈斯群岛发现了一种蓝色的小章鱼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cute-little-guy-scientists-discover-a-tiny-blue-species-of-octopus-by-the-galapagos-islands-180988919/</link><description>这种手掌大小的生物是在十多年前的一次研究探险中发现并收集的，但科学家们刚刚将其鉴定为之前未描述过的物种</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 18:33:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cute-little-guy-scientists-discover-a-tiny-blue-species-of-octopus-by-the-galapagos-islands-180988919/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚当局破纪录地查获了超过 100,000 只非法外来蟑螂</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/more-than-100000-illegal-exotic-cockroaches-were-seized-by-australian-authorities-in-a-record-setting-bug-bust-180988913/</link><description>据澳大利亚气候变化、能源、环境和水部称，这些昆虫的价值估计高达 141,000 美元。外来蟑螂可能危害该国的野生动物和农业</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/more-than-100000-illegal-exotic-cockroaches-were-seized-by-australian-authorities-in-a-record-setting-bug-bust-180988913/</guid></item><item><title>巨石阵的祭坛石是如何获得的？新研究加剧了人类活动与冰川运输之间的争论</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-stonehenge-get-its-altar-stone-new-research-reveals-evidence-adding-to-the-debate-between-human-effort-and-glacier-transport-180988918/</link><description>冰流模型和地质分析表明，在上一个冰河时代，冰川可能携带着这块石头走了一段路。然而，科学家表示这种情况不太可能发生</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 22:33:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-did-stonehenge-get-its-altar-stone-new-research-reveals-evidence-adding-to-the-debate-between-human-effort-and-glacier-transport-180988918/</guid></item><item><title>踪迹相机照片捕捉到肯尼亚森林中的稀有羚羊，保护主义者曾担心它们已经消失</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/trail-camera-photos-capture-rare-antelopes-in-a-kenya-forest-where-conservationists-once-feared-they-had-vanished-180988904/</link><description>据信野外生活的山地邦戈鼓不足 100 只，新发现揭示了这种极度濒危生物的重要栖息地</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 20:38:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/trail-camera-photos-capture-rare-antelopes-in-a-kenya-forest-where-conservationists-once-feared-they-had-vanished-180988904/</guid></item><item><title>这些意大利青少年在学校过夜。他们在地下室发现了古罗马遗址</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-italian-teenagers-stayed-overnight-at-their-school-they-found-ancient-roman-ruins-hidden-in-the-basement-180988917/</link><description>罗马一所高中的学生偶然发现了一栋保存完好的别墅，其历史可以追溯到公元二世纪中叶。最终，考古学家希望向公众开放这片广阔的空间</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 20:01:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-italian-teenagers-stayed-overnight-at-their-school-they-found-ancient-roman-ruins-hidden-in-the-basement-180988917/</gui